"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"### \\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/LFeku-vNnFwCuGZ-eJXhj.jpg?height=3840&width=3840)\\n\\n### Today, I was discussing my impressions of Chinese culture with my friends. I thought for a long time that what flashed in my mind were specific things. I tried to look at the clouds and mist to see how I feel. This is difficult because I can’t tell which ones are my own knowledge and which ones are. I was educated and influenced by the concept. Before I talk about my impression of Chinese culture, let me talk about the electronic synthesizer-style music album China created in 1979 by the Italian music master vangelis, which I like very much. This is a work that is rarely heard by people, and it is also a masterpiece worthy of our reflection. There is a piece of The Tao of Love that is often used in martial arts TV dramas in the 80s and 90s. The lingering and profound emotions conveyed by the music like It is the infinite yearning for the ancient and mysterious Eastern civilization. This is also my reaction to seeing ancient objects occasionally, what a fascinating civilized society, the passage of time will only deepen its mystery.\\n\\n \\n \\n\\n今天和朋友在讨论到对中华文化的印象。我想了很久脑海中闪现的都是具体的东西，我试着拨开云雾去看到我究竟是怎么看待的，这很难，因为我已经分不太清哪些是我自己的认识，哪些是我被教育和影响的观念。在先谈我对中华文化的印象之前，我先谈我很喜欢的意大利音乐大师vangelis在1979年创作的电子合成器风格的音乐专辑China 。这是一张很少被人听到的作品，也是值得我们去深思的杰作，里面有一首The Tao of Love被80，90的武侠电视剧经常用到，音乐传达的那种缠绵高深的情绪，像是对古老神秘东方文明的无限向往。这也是我偶尔看到古代的物件的反应，那是多么令人神往的文明社会，时间的流逝只会加深它的神秘感。（1.1）\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/zRC5s4nH9yGNa81Ol-pRq.jpg?height=3840&width=3840&size=large)\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/2YtTh96Nt2eeeJxWfKvX9.jpg?height=3840&width=3840&size=large)\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/6_ejqfPRRsKtjuqA6lhAm.jpg?height=3840&width=3840&size=large)\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/ke70E6glebZv9dABLTR-h.jpg?height=3840&width=3840&size=l